  <span id="freeText11142440865253761149" style="display:none">I am sharing this book with a very dear to me person, for the day has come when I am giving my gift to my third Mom (my mentor Tatiana Petrovna Babak). I know she will use it well . She already knows that the only things that matter are those made not of tin and glass, but of truth and joy and with the help of the birds: I still keep her knitted swallow - continuation of Bach's Seagull, (I) believe - she gave my daughter as a present from her granddaughters. You will ask me why am I giving this ring to the person who already knows the truth. Because her beloved husband's death has crashed her so fragile heart. Fragile? - you will ask. - Yes, because she has just forgotten the truth. And this ring for sure will bring her belief and truth back, for ever and ever. Then shall we be, as busy as a bee, if we live, or if we flee - updated from Ethel Lillian Voynich "Dear Jim", which updates William Blake "Song of experience. The fly": their ("Then am I a happy fly, if I live or if I die" ) now reads as follows: "Then shall we be as busy as a bee, if we live or if we flee!" to the place which is better than far away - our get-together ,,</span>
