<span id="freeTextContainer12965450305267289838">I found this book while working in a bookstore in CO. My family has lived in Indiana for a few decades give or take. So I was living very far from home. I had never been farther away than 15 min drive tops. And we moved 18 hrs away. I found this book and IIRC it is sorta more about someone dying than just distance. But my point is, my dad growing up had me read Jonathon Livingston Seagull. And to us that book was about rising above what others expectations are of you and make of your life what y</span>
  <span id="freeText12965450305267289838" style="display:none">I found this book while working in a bookstore in CO. My family has lived in Indiana for a few decades give or take. So I was living very far from home. I had never been farther away than 15 min drive tops. And we moved 18 hrs away. I found this book and IIRC it is sorta more about someone dying than just distance. But my point is, my dad growing up had me read Jonathon Livingston Seagull. And to us that book was about rising above what others expectations are of you and make of your life what you want. And what you envison. So finding this by Richard Bach and meaning behind this work was just kismet. I feel like this might go unappreciated by a lot of people if not introduced as a tool for when they need it. 😌</span>
